	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 1st 1:47 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, I know, alot of people say "if you want to solo, play a necro!" But guess what? I could care less what they think. Anyway, here is something I did with my enchanter from lvl 41 to 45 fairly quickly.<br>This really isn't a strategy, but more like a "try this out" post.<br><br>Well, I personally hardly ever travel to the Karana's or Qeynos for any reason, so one day while I was running around bored out of my mind, I saw this lone guard tower by the QH zone. I run up to the tower(at that moment I wasn't KoS yet), and con the guards, one is green, the other is blue. So I think "what the hell, why not" and pull the guard with the standard, tashani. I then proceed to root, dot once(to keep his hp from climbing too much between nukes), and nuke. After root breaks, just root and nuke as needed til he's dead. I lvl'd from 41 to 45 in 4 days since the guard is on a 6 minute spawn timer.<br><br>P.S. You will become KoS in Qeynos, and the Karana's by doing this. So if you care about faction, don't do it.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
