	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are working your way up as an enchanter, it is of some importance to tank some hits for your animation solo every once in a while.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>It doesnt take too many hits with ones high intelligence to get the five defense points per level.  I was actually amazed just how good of an AC an enchanter can have if they work on it a little bit each level.<br><br>The key however is to not miss any levels.  If you miss a few levels then the game is practically over and you will need help to gain those points.  It also helps to have a set of AC equipment(much of which is inexpensive) for your 1/2 bubble of tanking.  <br><br>One method of keeping your AC up in the mid levels is to pick on blue centaurs.  First you have to get sotw(not hard, just bribe a druid with breeze or clarity) then let them shoot you in the back.  The damage they do with their arrows is not tremendous so you can milk each centaur for quite a while.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
