	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've actually had the most luck grouped with a bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their versitility in any given situation makes for a good partner, IMHO.  They have the ability to snare, albeit not as effective as a druid/ranger it still gets the job done.  If fear/snare is not possible given the location or closeness of other mobs, tanking is still possible - but only if yer willing to pay for it runes you'll need to cast.  This really only becomes a viable option at 34 when you get yer Rune 3.  The other runes simply can't hold up to the dmg delt.  But with Rune 3, and above, I can effectively keep the bard at full health.  Any health loss is recovered quickly with a health song.  And downtime due to mana is really not a problem given clarity w/ mana song.  This is also a noteworthy place for yer pet.  Have the bard pull with the least amount of dmg possible and tashan as you see the mob coming.  99% of the time the mob will hit you, pet will aggro and taunt, and the fight can begin.  With a Rune on yourself you've still not received any dmg. And if this begin to go horribly wrong, just mez, if possible, play a little Selo and leaves yer troubles behind.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
