	   <tr><td colspan=2>Please allow me for a moment to make a few points and pose a few questions, I hope we will all be a bit better off.<br><br>1.<br>Ok, what is an enchanter? We are the crowd control experts and the only people that can other people gain mana faster...<br><br>2.<br>What is the most mana efficient way to spend mana in this game (if you are familiar with this game at all you know that efficiency and mana are 2 things that you cannot live without)?&nbsp;&nbsp;Again, as an enchanter you know the answer is in Mezmerizing a target.<br><br>3.<br>So what do you do when you can't mez a target (IE: puller managed to get only 1 or the others are already enthralled or better)?<br><br>4.<br>Melee damage and healing is also extremely efficient. Warriors Take the least amount of damage in the game per hit (read the warrior boards) and clerics heal the best in the game at higher levels (read their boards). When I say best I mean the most efficient.<br><br>5.<br>Improving efficiency is something you are striving for otherwise you would not be reading these boards ;)<br><br>6.<br>How would you like to save the cleric Half of his mana, Heck, Not even that, 30% of his mana?<br><br>7.<br>30% more mana for cleric = 30% more mana for everyone ;).<br><br>8.<br>The main point, Slowing is the single most effective spell line in the game when your party is only being attacked by 1 target.<br><br>9.<br>If you have a ranger in your group who also is the one handling snares or laying in a dd or 2 they will love you because they can get off spells while being hit (although don't let rangers be tanks they aren't)<br><br>10.<br>If you have a Paladin or SK in your group they will also love you as their spells are able to be cast during battle. Although the SK would love you more as they cast more during the heat of battle as an average.<br><br>11.<br>Your Fellow Casters will love you, Depending on Level and equipment we die in about 20 - 30 seconds with the MOB targeting us. Why not extend that time to 30 - 45 seconds, it will give the tanks much more time to taunt off of us, or the overnuking wizard (although wizards aren't very efficient unless you count the evacs which save you bubbles of mana hehe).<br><br>12. <br>Your Monks and Rogues will love you. They like rangers are not supposed to take damage. If they take damgage it will be more than the tank would take, So don't let them get hit, if they only get swung at 60% of the time, they will save a ton of hp.<br><br>13. Warriors will love you because they take tons of damage in a fight, bards will love you because they can start singing again, perhaps to turn on selos and save the entire group.<br><br>14. Ok you read through it all, sorry for the length. If you group with a shaman, Let him cast slow, most of the time he has a better spell, however, research the spells at say eq.castersrealm.com oftentimes we have an equal spell. IF you are only pulling 1 mob at a time (monk pulling) and have additional mana to spend, don't waste on something like a damage shield to give your tank 100 more hp, give him 1000 more hp with the slow spell.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
