	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alright assuming you are level 20 you already know that you are doing a lot of crowd control, If not then you should start.<br>&lt;rant on&gt;<br>STOP SOLOING FOR PETES SAKE PEOPLE, C'MON NO NEED TO POST GUIDES FOR SOLOING INTO THE 30s IF YOU WANT TO SOLO DON'T PLAY AN ENCHANTER.<br>&lt;rant off&gt;<br><br>Ok sorry if I offended everyone with my shouting, but I have a few more valid points. It is not often you will find a good puller, therefore, You will need to mezmerize more often. Mezmerize is THE most efficient spell in the game(well the upgrades are better of course).<br><br>However, if you always group with a monk (they usually only pull 1, and 2 if unlucky, then you should be great with not specializing in Conjuration. However, if you are into pick-me up groups alot, or find yourself casting mez type spells 3 or 4 times a fight, then you could very well pick conj. to place as your primary specialization. Now, All you have to do is ask yourself which do you cast more, MEZ, OR EVERYTHING else. Perhaps at 20 its everything else, but at 25 it will become Mez, its not super duper hard to change your specialization in it.<br><br>Lastly, Specialization is going to hurt you too much if your specialize in one and not another, Remember you still get 50 skill points in all of them, So don't worry one way or the other. You definatly do not have to wait till 50 to put your primary at conj. unless of course you are a bad enchanter. (sorry if I offend you please don't hate me too bad). However, at 20 it may not be the best choice to go to conj as well. Its a personal choice, and either one can be good, just like choosing High Elves or Erudites. (ouch sorry if I offended you inkies shorties, and cows, I mean humans)<br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
