	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, Perhaps I got off topic a bit, I was tired and not thinking clearly, I certainly did not wish to have my post taken as an anti-soloing post. I do love enchanters ability to solo, and we are the BEST at dual-spawning camps, and can easily take 3 spawn camps under certain conditions. This I am not denying. However...<br><br>Soloing does not get you noticed, soloing does not put you on friends lists, and soloing does not allow an enchanter to practice his grouping skills.<br><br>This is not something unique to enchanters. I recommend Everyone in the game at least group with 1 other person. Necromancers even.&nbsp;&nbsp;2 people taking down 1 mob, or 2 mobs(with 1 being mezzed) will get the job down with less effort than 2 people seperatly taking down the 2 mobs.<br><br>Its not an exact science, but basically a group of 2 people can do the work of 2 and a half. Earning 2 and a half times the exp for 2 times the number of people.<br><br>6 people can earn probly close to 10 times the amount of exp for 6 times the amount of people. This is because the mobs only attack one person at a time. Dividing and conquering, as well as a blitzkreig are very obvious military terms that can be applied here.  <br><br>This Is my post on Soloing vs grouping.<br><br><br>My previous post was on specialization, I hope you read it as that...<br><br>besides, I mentioned that most soloers should go with alteration, and when you do decide to go into group combat (around 20 I believe for most people) you will find that mez is a much more commonly cast spell, perhaps more than any other (besides perhaps a buff, or slowdown, again its all depending on the situation.<br><br>Repeat I did not mean to imply that soloing was not something capable of enchanters, mearly to say that we could be providing so much more to the playing experience of 5 other people.<br><br>Well whatever you decide to do, Enjoy it ;)<br><br>and as for the original poster, I hope you got my message that you won't go wrong either way, and that either way you will be happy.  And if you are ever grouped with an enchanter that chose differently than you, mearly let him cast the mez spells, or you take charge of the mez spells, but again its all just relative to your position.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ezzlan 25th ENC Brell<br>Antarius 35th Bard Terris-Thule</td></tr>
