	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alteration is by far the most popular choice. Just the number of spells that use the skill is enough justification. That, coupled with the usefulness of certain spells in combat situations for your mid levels, lead most to this choice.<br> As you progress in levels and you become more of the "traffic cop" type player, you may want to change your specialty. The Mesmerize spell line uses conjuration and if you find that that is ALL you really do, the quest to change is there to complete.<br><br>Whatever you choose, you will not be "stuck" with your choice. Alteration is probably the best choice until level 50 when most all MoBs will have a magic resist high enough to make a lot of your&nbsp;&nbsp;debuffs and DoTs next to useless. At that point you can quest to change so your Mesmerisation spells are more efficent.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sobur<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Dying with style, in a zone near you...</td></tr>
