	   <tr><td colspan=2>With the recently added 'pause' command, a bard may now do one complete 3 song twist, all inside one social. Unfortunately, using these socials doesn't let you adapt to any situations, and if you fizzle (or sing a wrong note), the social pause-timing is thrown out of whack.<br><br>I tried to make a chain stun myself, where I would press the social, cast stun, wait 3 seconds, cast another stun, wait 6 seconds, and cast another stun. Unfortunately, if there were any resists or fizzles, I would be unable to cast -anything- during the pause time. Be careful how you use it.<br><br>Taern<br>Level 41 Enchanter<br>Lanys T'vyl<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
