	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm an enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;I try to use my pet only when the group I'm in is lacking in the tank dept. (like a single monk) and the extra melee is needed or when i'm forced to solo, because I've been burned too many times using charm.  When using it in a group, however, try to get hit first.  When the puller comes back with the monster, throw a tashan spell on it (which should be your first spell anyhow) and try to intervene.  Take the hit, and get back.  If your pet attacks a monster that walks in and whacks you while the party is already engaged, you'll be unable to mez the new opponent and your pet is likely to bite the dust.  And if that means you do get whacked by another creature a time or two more, no big deal, after its mez'd, your pet will attack it as soon as its done with what the monster its currently on.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
