<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96712847811384></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96712847811384><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96712847811384>RE: Working in a group</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96712847811384#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=353><span id=Sage>Tehom</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>135 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 24th 10:47 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At low levels, there are various tricks you can use to do your job while not endangering yourself.<br>Use, in different instances, root, fear, charm, and color stuns. None of these are perfect - root is easily broken by nukes, fear has the danger of bringing back more, a dotted charm is a menace, and color stuns can be both expensive and high-taunters. However, in a group that still hasn't learned the joys of /assist or not to wake up mobs, these can be invaluable. Depending on the situation, you will find one of the above options more valuable than the other choices - and generally far preferable to getting killed by another broken mez.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
